Name: Move Counter
Brief Summary of Comments: -Every method looks to be implemented correctly however we will have to make sure once the overall game features are done - Spelling mistakes (increment and decrement) please fix!

Name: Extreme Agents
Brief Summary of Comments:
The OrderQueue class does not have an initializer, which means its <orders> attribute
will be null all the time. Add an initializer for the class.

Name: Null Object Pattern
Brief Summary of Comments: -Real Moves Counter initializer should not be public and should be protected/private and static since client should not be able to instantiate more than 1 object of this. NullObject class looks fine.

Name: Custom Movement Behaviours
Brief Summary of Comments: Good use of using the strategy pattern by isolating each movement behaviour into its own class. Code looks clean, well organized and easy to follow. Goof job.

Name: Moves Counter
Brief Summary of Comments: Please make the instant attribute "moves" and the method "incrementMoves" static so that the AddMoves class can access them without creating a new "MovesCounter" instance.

Name: Mystery Box
Brief Summary of Comments: Every method and class seems to be correct however I suggest you use a helper function in MysteryBox.java since the if else statements do very similar things.
